General Notes: 
CREATED DATE: Mar 10 2009  5:29PM
Jobs at Nunwood:
For all Recruitment Agencies 
At Nunwood, we are currently increasing our direct applicants every month, and this is something we want to continue with for years to come. We get a huge amount of calls per day from recruitment agencies and it is very difficult to keep in contact with everyone of them. 

We have a PSL (Preferred Suppliers List) in place that we have worked very hard to build and maintain relationships with. At the moment we are not looking to review this PSL. 

If you wish to contact us, and build a working relationship €“ please follow these instructions: 
€¢	Firstly, you must have a candidate who fits all the criteria explained in our job specifications 
€¢	The candidate will have been fully interviewed and referenced (personnel and professional) 
€¢	Your candidate will send a cover note as to why they would like to be submitted for a role with us 
€¢	You will be in agreement with our Terms and Conditions €“ please follow this link 
€¢	Once you have agreed to our Terms and Conditions please send the candidates details to  emmacarter-smith@nunwood.com 
Please only send the best candidates who fully match the job specification. 

Other notes to acknowledge:
€¢	You will never advertise on our behalf with our company logo 
€¢	If we receive a CV from you that does not fulfil the above, we are not able to consider the application 
€¢	Temporary and Contract Workers €“ We do not take on Temporary or Contract workers at any time 
€¢	If you decide to call us we will ask you to email your details over €“ we do not take cold calls from agencies who aren€™t on our PSL 
€¢	Should you wish to send your details over for when we review our PSL €“ please email them to
 emmacarter-smith@nunwood.com 
We will file your details and will refer to them in case we need help in the future. Please do not call us €“ we will call you if our situation changes or we require help filling a vacancy. 

In your email please specify which areas you specialise in: 

If you do call us consistently and don€™t follow our guidelines we will blacklist your agency €“ while this is not our preferred method for dealing with agencies, we want to concentrate our energies on people who apply who really want to work for us 
Kind regards
Kerah

General Notes: 
CREATED DATE: Oct 28 2009 10:33AM
LR 16/03/15 Signed terms at 15% with Emma Bunn (HR Officer) via Rob Gordon who is Head of BA and who Steve and I placed with back when he was with LV. Released 6 BA Permanent jobs (Business Change) for their Chelsmford office (if we prove ourselves here we will get the London roles released via Michalea John). They are moving office in Chelmsford which has capacity for 750 heads so they are going to be very busy in terms of recruitment! The office is walking distance from the station.

CV/ Interview process - Must fill out their Coversheet (on E Drive under Coversheets) conference call with Emma and Rob Gordon, then onto Assessment centre cosniting of 1 hour F2F,  1 hr case study,  Half hour prep to conduct 15 minute presentation and then 15 minute Q&A. If that goes well they will have a further meeting with Rob for rubber stamp. They have extremely high standards and likes canddiates from Insurance or Financial Regulatory body. **We must meet / Skype go beyond a quick 10 minute chat with all candidates. **Benefits are good, they pay shares to emplyees, bonus, healthcare, pension, 25 days holiday etc.

ONLY WAY IN IS THROUGH MANAGERS - work with Huntress. Michaela is like a brick wall. Michaela and Ravinder are our best HR contacts, Christ Tingle has never to my knowledge answered his phone. Not once! Amlin are a big underwriter that work on the Lloyds london market

General Notes: 
CREATED DATE: Apr 19 2017  8:20AM
2 roles with these guys at director level, one within OMD and one with sister company, PHD.

The roles are a mixture of of marketing science and Data Science and will involve taking a lead position within a team of around 10, made up of graduate and senior members of the team.

They're not after an out and out data scientist at all; more someone who has the skills that work around Julian and Andy's existing set - namely solid experience around macro-analytics and trend analysis for Julian and Econometrics without MMM specialisation for Andy's.

They want 3-4 years of solid management experience of SENIOR staff for both and to be, on the whole, making business decisions and strategically thinking, Hands-on when needed but they're not looking for someone to do the dirty work at this stage, that's what the 10 man team is for.

Role itself can be summarised as the 'Lead econometrician and 2nd Strategic Thinker within the company'. BD required in that you will be expected to lead pitches for new clients so string communication skills and client-facing ability is essential.

Work/life balance is very good for an agency and you'd be working for the best media agency in the country as per the massive amounts of awards.

80k but will stretch for the right person

Product:

•             Provide 24hr solution support and international implementation.

Produce bespoke work for cutomers;

o             They have people working on the development add on.

o             People looking after the bespoke work.

*Infor sunsystem: is a powerful financial management solution, designed to map to your business. It is a comprehensive international accounting and financial reporting system, proven by 9,000 customers in over 190 countries. SunSystems includes multi-currency, multi-language, multi-chart of accounts, multi-accounting treatments and real-time reporting and analysis.

 

Feature:

•             Offices across Europe, US, Asia and, Australia.

•             Clients: logistics, distribution, insurance

Office:

·         Great location

·         Open plan office

·         View of London Bridge

·         Light office

·         12 people in US

·         11 people in Manchester

Work Culture

·         Sit in teams

·         Run apprenticeships

·         Quiz nights

·         Cake sales

·         5 o’clock beer fridge on Fridays

·         Number one Rule: None one shouts/swears in public(office)

·         Chance to move abroad

·         Gym membership, pension scheme, healthcare.

Direct Competitors:

·         Touchstone

·         Codestone

·         In4

·         IIS-microsoft

Experience:

.net as per spec THEY DONT NEED SAP one

·          “SAP one” isn’t SAP as we know it – so don’t have the misconception these are sap role cos 1 million % aren’t they aren’t.

·         SAP Business one – ERP system (not essential but preferred)

Looking to take on 25 candidates over the next year. Junior/Senior roles. Agreed 15% terms.

.Net: 

·         5 open roles

·         Want people who can build models unique to Sapphire which gives them an edge over their competitors. This is all to improve the functionality of business one.

·         Looking for very good coms

Interview Stage:

·         1 or 2 stages potentially just one- could hire on the spot.

·         Want email marketing Executive role ASAP- if good candidate could start on Monday.

CREATED DATE: Feb 14 2014 12:43PM


~~The Pool Re scheme has been set up by the insurance industry in co-operation with the UK government so that  insurers can continue to cover losses resulting from damage caused by acts of terrorism to commercial property in Great Britain.

Insurers that participate in the scheme offer terrorism cover as part of the relevant commercial policies they issue when their policyholders request them to do so. Each insurer must pay losses up to a threshold, which is determined individually for that insurer. When losses exceed that threshold, the insurer can claim upon reserves accumulated by the insurance industry on a mutual basis within a separate company, Pool Reinsurance Company Limited (€œPool Re€). Should terrorism claims exceed these reserves, Pool Re can, in turn, draw funds from government to enable it to meet its obligations in full, regardless of the scale of losses.

NB: They do not have a company contact number or a full address, so give Ian Coward (Head of IT) a call.

They do have a PSL.

General Notes: 
CREATED DATE: May 23 2017 10:10AM
hierachy of Prophet:


Hierarchy is always a harder thing to explain here, as we have quite a flat structure with very different responsibilities at each level.

The main levels within the business are:
€¢	Associate
€¢	Senior Associate
€¢	Engagement Manager
€¢	Senior Engagement Manager
€¢	Associate Partner
€¢	Partner
€¢	Senior Partner

As the job description mentioned, this role would come in at the EM level, so, in terms of responsibility, would be a strong technician who also has the ability to lead engagements and the relevant teams,  as well as acting as advisor both externally to clients and internally to Partners. The Managers tend to be the real day to day leads and an Insights Manager is likely to be working closely with a Generalist Manager, alongside the client.

I hope this helps explain things a little more but do let me know if they have any more questions

CREATED DATE: Jul  8 2014  2:02PM
PERFORMLY - IPG Mediabrands product

HOW TO SELL:

Performly is a product that puts value on social media likes, follows, shares etc. This is the data that will be visualized.

Currently only uses data from Facebook, Twitter, Youtube – any candidate with social media exp will jump up in the queue.

Clients who are using it: Unilver, Microsoft, Ferrari, Deutsche Bank (Coca Cola in final talks)

This product is so popular that currently IPG is declining new business because they cannot cope with demand.

PERFECT CANDIDATES:

Knowledge of social media.

Media agency background

Dot com startup background – strong preference

*Data visualization – send examples of work with CVs

*Application Support – apps related to social media 

DATA VISUALIZATION DEVELOPER x1 around the 55k – will consider more if exceptional as urgent


	Very strong web dev background / web based dashboards
	Visualizations done with the Web Dev languages etc. Javascript, d3, JQuery, HTML,CSS, Bootstrap
	Tableau – its a secondary skill / v strong web dev visualization people without Tableau WILL be considered
	Working with Malaysia, NYC, San Fran teams – good comms needed



APPLICATION SUPPORT ANALYST x1 around 45k – preferably less


	1st Line support / application support experience crucial
	Social media exposure big preference
	Great customer service for clients from different countries
	Microsoft environment
	Knowledge (theoretical) of Tableau, ASP.NET, C#, VB.net, Jquery, Javascrip, html5, CSS3, Ajax
	Desired: SQL Server 2008; Advanced Excel
	Product is based on the above techs so understanding of them is important

General Notes: 
CREATED DATE: Jun 23 2014  8:24AM
The interview takes five parts:

1)      Introduction to the Rated People business, the team and questions about your knowledge of it

2)      You will be asked to take Tim and Katy through your CV and position your achievements in the context of the job role at Rated.

3)      Tim and Katy will then ask you to describe your role in three different situations or projects you have worked on €“ classic behavioural interview questions. You should cover the background to the project/situation you have chosen.   What did you do? How did you do it? Why? What was the outcome? 

4)      They will ask you a quick skills question.

5)      Then there is time for you to ask questions of Tim and Katy.

 

We are looking for people that are confident, able to express themselves in a logical and coherent way. If they haven€™t heard or don€™t understand the question that isn€™t a problem they should ask for it to be repeated.

General Notes: 
CREATED DATE: Oct 24 2014 10:01AM
http://www.pnmsoft.com/resources/videos/bill-gates-on-sequence/

Pnm soft is a growing software house with roughly 200 employees across four countries, New Jersey, Watford, Israel and Ireland? They are a Microsoft gold partner and tipped by bill gates and Gartner for greatness, currently doubling in size year on year they sell business process management solutions to some of the worlds largest companies (kpmg for example).

The are looking for strong technical candidates who have good interpersonal skills to work in a friendly ambitious team delivering software solutions in a client facing role, you will need to be a great communicator and have thoroughly researched the company and re the role at first interview stage, 2nd interview is 30 mins interview, tech multiple choice test 50 % is a decent mark it is hard. Then a one hour coding test, you'll have the reference material. If this goes well another interview and offer. The client is desperate for people and need to see some options.

It is a great company to work for, they have great people to learn from and the projects will be for big name companies but in a smaller dynamic team. They are very sociable and work the business owners and directors how are highly energised in this exciting growth phase.

General Notes: 
CREATED DATE: Jan  6 2016  1:04PM
LR 06/01/2016 Very successful creditscoring / consumer finance startup founded by Justin Bansani circa 1 year old and just won the "Innovator of the Year award for 2015". Client gained through my old contact Klaus Thorup who is CTO. 15% agreed fees with 2 weeks exclusivity on all roles. Moving from Hammersmith to Lambeth bridge (in between Vauxhall and Waterloo) on 25th January 2016 to massive office over 2 floors complete with pool table / lounge area and room to grow considerably. They have just about hit the 1 million customer mark and have just launched their mobile app before Christmas which has been hugely popular top 3 financial app. They have just taken on our contractor on a permanent basis as the QA Lead (Paul Bellchambers). 

Dan Page (looks after front end dev / deign recruitment), Dan McEvoy looks after backend development / devops recruitment. James Mantle looks after analytics / anything else!
 

Benefits:

	         Holidays – 25 paid holidays and a “duvet day” on your birthday
	         Pension – 3% contribution
	         Health Insurance 
	         Perk box – a choice of different benefits ranging from deals on restaurants, shopping, cinema, mobile insurance, childcare tax relief, cycle to work
	         Additional – flexible work hours, working from home, free breakfast and fruit, company paid beer fridge, pool table, tabletennis, monthly company events, Friday lunches paid, funky new offices in SE1

CREATED DATE: Feb 22 2017  4:33PM

€œ€Test is giving her a csv file with a load of customer spend data. 
There are no major tricks or traps - we ask one basic question and give her 1.5hrs to answer this and anything else she may think is important.
We ask that she brings her own laptop if possible. Also bring some headphones as she will likely be working an open area of the office. 

We're testing prioritisation and communication skills as much as actual analytics. 

Not at a stage to discuss salary yet - but in our team we all have flat salaries (no bonus) and some deliveroo equity (standard terms of 4 year vesting, 1 yr cliff). Pensions are coming and will be 'pretty good' for a young company - but I don't have an ETA on when they're landing.
We also offer loads of free food on Fridays, equipment of choice (i.e top specced macs), subsidised gym membership (and general access to a high volume of food)€€

General Notes: 
CREATED DATE: Apr 14 2016  3:16PM
Gotham Digital Science (GDS) is an international security services company specializing in Application and Network Infrastructure security, and Information Security Risk Management. GDS clients number among the largest financial services institutions and software development companies in the world.

GDS security specialists work with clients to assess risk and then design, build, and maintain secure applications, networks, and processes. With offices located in New York City and London, GDS seamlessly and efficiently assists clients with operations on both sides of the Atlantic.

In the United Kingdom GDS is a member of the UK industry body CREST (the Council of Registered Ethical Security Testers) as well as a member of the UK Government CHECK scheme, allowing GDS to provide security assurance services to Her Majesty's Government and UK Critical National Infrastructure on systems processing protectively marked information.

CREATED DATE: Apr 15 2016  9:55AM
Arcanum IS Ltd provides independent specialist security services through the G-Cloud for your Public Service Network (PSN). All of our security consultants are security cleared, UK based and most are CLAS registered. We have considerable experience and expertise in providing: Security Accreditation Services for IL2-IL6 networks; Technical Security Risk Assessments; Risk Management and Accreditation Document Sets; Privacy Impact Assessments; Risk Balance Cases; HMG Information Assurance Standards & Policy advice including the Security Policy Framework & CESG Standards & Policy; Security Audits to ISO 27001; Secure Architecture Design; Computer Forensics; Security Incident Management; Security Requirements; Business Continuity Planning; IT Health Checks, Penetration Testing and reports; Physical Security Surveys and Reports
